SETSPEED level

	sets how fast the turtle animates its movements.  The input is
	a number from 0 to 10.  0 (the default) means no animation:  the
	turtle and its drawing jump instantly to the result.  1 is the
	slowest visible speed and 10 is the fastest; in between, the
	turtle is shown walking along each line as it draws.  Levels
	above 10 are treated as 10.  See SPEED.
